<title>MEXICO: Banco de Mexico to drain 4.287 bln pesos.</title>
<headline>Banco de Mexico to drain 4.287 bln pesos.</headline>
<dateline>MEXICO CITY 1997-07-03</dateline>
<text>
<p>Banco de Mexico sought to drain 4.287 billion pesos from the secondary market on Thursday through a combination of three direct sales of paper and six repurchase agreements, dealers said.</p>
<p>The Cetes sales were offered as follows:</p>
<p>    AMOUNT     TERM</p>
<p>    150 million    364 days</p>
<p>    150 million    181 days</p>
<p>    150 million     91 days</p>
<p>The terms and maturities of the repurchase agreements were offered as follows:</p>
<p>    600 million     64 days</p>
<p>    700 million     49 days</p>
<p>    750 million     43 days</p>
<p>    750 million     21 days</p>
<p>    850 million     19 days</p>
<p>    187 million	1 day</p>
<p>*Amounts in pesos</p>
<p>(( --Mexico City newsroom +525 728-9559))</p>
